 Director, Product Management			Health Care Product Development			The Advisory Board Company www.advisory.com *LI			Keywords: product owner, product manager, customer experience, patient experience, customer journey, patient journey, customer relationship management, CRM, data science, propensity models, predictive analytics, machine learning, health IT 			The Director, Product Management will serve as the Customer Experience domain expert and analytics product owner. The position is responsible for leading a team of product managers and data scientists through the development and delivery of a new solution that influences the customer journey throughout the health care customer lifecycle. The role requires an individual with strong analytical and communication skills, high adaptability, strong domain expertise, as well as an entrepreneurial mindset and product management skills. This individual is primarily responsible for creating a distinctive product vision, managing the multi-year product roadmap, and creating an effective engineering partnership to deliver a market-leading solution. This is a unique opportunity to lead a growing team within the Health Care Technology organization and work with the most progressive health systems in the country. 			The Director of Product Management will report to the VP, Product Management for Health Care Technology, and will work closely with the General Manager, Strategy Lead, and Development team for the Customer/Patient Experience domain. 			The position is based out of our Washington, DC office  What You'll Be Doing:			- Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to create a distinctive product vision for an analytic platform to improve the end-to-end patient experience, omni-channel marketing and customer acquisition strategies			- Translate product vision into an executable roadmap for the core product, and continue to refine product vision over time based on feedback from users, domain experts and the market			- Own the success against product and business KPIs (working in concert with business owners)			- Partner with UX strategy, product design, and data science colleagues to lead product discovery, usability, and user research workshops to ensure that we are building high value, usable and desired features			- Partner with data science colleagues to apply advanced analytic techniques such as predictive and prescriptive modeling (e.g. sentiment, propensity, segmentation, clustering, retention, persistency/churn, long-term profitability, etc.)			- Translate market analysis, user feedback, and competitive analysis into the agile development process (i.e., user stories, annotated wireframes, etc.)			- Oversee the development backlog, prioritizing new features, enhancements and defects against clear business priorities			- Oversee the rollout of predictable, high-quality product releases			- Collaborate with commercial colleagues on product go-to-market strategy, and support the commercial pipeline as pre-sales technical and domain expert			- Provide internal and external stakeholders with the appropriate updates on progress, vision, product roadmap, etc.  Must Haves: 			- Education: Bachelor's Degree			- 9+ years of professional experience delivering software products			- 5+ years of product management experience for a consumer software product or service			- Proven experience managing a high performing team of 3+ direct reports			- Demonstrable understanding of CRM technology and customer experience 			- Demonstrable understanding of the SDLC and agile methodologies			- Experience with consumer products or digital strategy			- Proven ability to manage a complex array of internal and external stakeholders			- Proven ability to boil down market findings into new product/enhancement ideas  Even Better:  			- 1+ years of enterprise software product management experience in health IT			- 1+ years of data science or machine learning experience			- Bachelor’s degree in a life science or physical science, computer science, mathematics, engineering, or related degree program 			- Master's degree in business, health care-related field, computer science, mathematics, informatics, or related degree program			- Proven ability to lead product discovery or other user-centric development techniques			- Proven track record managing and mentoring more junior product managers  About Advisory Board			Advisory Board is a best practices firm that uses a combination of research, technology, and consulting to improve the performance of 4,400+ health care organizations. Headquartered in Washington, D.C., with offices worldwide, Advisory Board forges and finds the best new ideas and proven practices from its network of thousands of leaders, then customizes and hardwires them into every level of member organizations, creating enduring value. For more information, visit www.advisory.com.  			 			We are a workplace that...      Values and celebrates diversity of experience, culture, and opinion			     Is committed to creating an inclusive environment to enhance our collective experience			     Promotes a supportive community through staff-led affinity groups, events, and education​  Our Culture & Values: 			We think Forbes said it best: “Making the world a better place is what The Advisory Board Company is all about.” We have a unique culture where employees are told to avoid after work emails, encouraged to take 10 hours per month of paid leave for community service, and are expected to add surplus value in every interaction with a member or colleague. 			 			Over the past thirty years, we have developed a distinctive corporate culture based on our values and principles. We award, promote, and praise based on individual performance, capabilities, and ambition. We provide ways for staff to share their time, talent, and passions in the community. We reward innovation and foster a collaborative environment. We have a performance-driven staff and peers that challenge one another in the workplace. And we want free-thinkers, agile speakers, witty writers, and team players to join the firm – at Advisory Board, your ideas are heard and your contributions matter.   Perks (A Few of Many):			Consistent with our belief that our employees are our most valuable resource, The Advisory Board Company offers a competitive benefits package.			- Medical, dental, and vision insurance, dependents eligible			- 401(k) retirement plan with company match			- 20+ days paid time off and 10+ paid company holidays			- Daytime leave policy for community service or fitness activities (up to 10 hours a month each)			- Wellness programs including gym discounts and incentives to promote healthy living			- Dynamic growth opportunities with merit-based promotion philosophy			- Benefits kick in day one, see the full details here			 
